"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-26-Former-Olympian-tells-athletes-Enjoy-every-moment-of-Paris-Games--1vy21zBCW0o-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  CGTN's Li Dongning spoke with China's first Winter Olympic champion, Yang Yang. In 2002, she won a gold medal at the Salt Lake City Games in the women's 500 meters in short track speed skating. She holds an impressive collection of 59 world championship titles, and she will serve at the Paris Games as the vice president of the World Anti-Doping Agency. Let us hear what she has to say to the Olympic athletes.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"